    "body": "This appears to be something about the Alchemy provider (I believe the public endpoint is backed by Alchemy as well though I could be wrong). \n\nWith a local op-geth (running a devnet in this case rather than goerli admittedly) depositNonce is included in the response:\n```\n\ncast receipt --json 0x6d0df35224d4f4da4148eddef4108aab250b31d39e3d5fff266a6b24f42d4711 --rpc-url http://localhost:9545 | jq\n{\n  \"transactionHash\": \"0x6d0df35224d4f4da4148eddef4108aab250b31d39e3d5fff266a6b24f42d4711\",\n  \"transactionIndex\": \"0x0\",\n  \"blockHash\": \"0x6c40d0349d4a6d51d088453a2812963738376434851f44fc0e9c38ad15fcab41\",\n  \"blockNumber\": \"0xb5\",\n  \"from\": \"0xdeaddeaddeaddeaddeaddeaddeaddeaddead0001\",\n  \"to\": \"0x4200000000000000000000000000000000000015\",\n  \"cumulativeGasUsed\": \"0xf9dd\",\n  \"gasUsed\": \"0xf9dd\",\n  \"contractAddress\": null,\n  \"logs\": [],\n  \"status\": \"0x1\",\n  \"logsBloom\": \"\",\n  \"type\": \"0x7e\",\n  \"effectiveGasPrice\": \"0x0\",\n  \"depositNonce\": \"0xb4\"\n}\n```",
